answer:
You can find a list of people eligible for the publicly funded (free) HPV9 vaccine on our HPV page. The publicly funded vaccine is available from public health units, some pharmacies and some doctors' offices. 
Those not eligible for the free HPV9 vaccine can purchase it at most pharmacies and travel clinics. The cost for the vaccine series (3 doses) is approximately $500. Some health insurance plans may cover the cost of the vaccine. 
- Immunization Nurse
